Rock Tutorials
--------------------------
Welcome to the ROCK tutorials. The tutorials are intended for a practicioners and developers in the robotics field to start working with the Robot Construction Kit. 
To be able to follow and get the most out of the tutorials, you should be familiar with basic software development strategies in C++. The tutorials will not teach you C++ or software development in general, but they provide you with a guideline for developing components for 
You will also benefit from a knowlegde of CMake, Ruby, pkg-config. 

What to expect from the tutorials
----------------------------
The tutorials are structured as follows.
The first set of tutorials covers 'Basics' and will teach you on how to create a library, embed into an Orocos component using orogen, and finally deploy it, i.e. build an run. 
The second set covers 'Logging and replay' and will allow you to extract data from running components. 
The third set convers 'Visualization and data analysis'
The complete set is wrapped up by a holistic example 'Rolling Rock'

